OL,3,CTemperatures set to plummet after
OL,4,Chottest day of the year so far
OL,6,FThe promised warm weather certainly
OL,7,Fdidn't disappoint this week as highs
OL,8,Fsoared 14C above the seasonal average
OL,9,Fto 26.6C - heat that forecasters
OL,10,Fcalled "exceptional".
OL,12,FBut the hottest day of the year so far
OL,13,Fwill soon become a warm memory, as
OL,14,Fcold Atlantic air is already starting
OL,15,Fto flood in from the northwest.JWhy
OL,16,Fare the temperatures dropping?
OL,18,FOnce again the answer, in large part,
OL,19,Fis down to wind direction.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
