OL,3,CTemperatures set to plummet after
OL,4,Chottest day of the year so far
OL,6,FThe soaring highs of Wednesday were
OL,7,Fmade possible by a warm southeasterly
OL,8,Fwind tapping into the pool of warm air
OL,9,Fsitting across the near continent.
OL,11,FThat warm air, added to plenty of
OL,12,Fsunshine, boosted temperatures far in
OL,13,Fexcess of the average for early April.
OL,15,FBut the winds are now veering
OL,16,Fnorthwesterly which will cut off that
OL,17,Ffeed of warm European air and instead
OL,18,Fdraw in something much colder from the
OL,19,Fnorth Atlantic.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1775718328
OL,3,CTemperatures set to plummet after
OL,4,Chottest day of the year so far
OL,6,FIn that colder air, temperatures will
OL,7,Fbe some 10 degrees cooler and much
OL,8,Fcloser to the seasonal average. In
OL,9,Fcomparison to the midweek heat it will
OL,10,Fcertainly feel like a shock to the
OL,11,Fsystem.
OL,13,FWill it get colder for everyone?
OL,15,FYes eventually, but because of the
OL,16,Fdirection of that wind, the colder air
OL,17,Fwill take longest to reach the
OL,18,Fsheltered far southeastern parts of
OL,19,FEngland.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
